==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stover
<hw>Sto"ver</hw> <pr>(st⟦omac⟧"v⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>estoveir</ets>, <ets>estovoir</ets>, necessity, provisions,
properly an inf., ⟦ldquo⟧to be necessary.⟦rdquo⟧ Cf.
<er>Estovers</er>.]</ety> <def>Fodder for cattle, especially straw or
coarse hay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where live nibbling sheep,⟦br⟧
And flat meads thatched with <qex>stover</qex> them to keep.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thresh barley as yet but as need shall require,⟦br⟧
Fresh threshed for <qex>stover</qex> thy cattle desire.</q>
<rj><qau>Tusser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stow</ent>⟦br⟧
